A LIMPOPO pastor alleged to have raped four minors appeared in the Lenyenye Magistrates Court yesterday.The thirty-two-year-old pastor was arrested by the SAPS Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Tzaneen after members of the community reported the allegations to the cops.The pastor, whose ministry is based in Burgersdorp just outside Nkowankowa in Tzaneen, allegedly raped four girls who were ushers at his church over a period of 10 months. He would allegedly invite the victims individually to the church for a prayer session, and then attack and rape them.Two of the girls are aged 14, while the other two are aged 12 and 16.He was denied bail and will remain in custody until his next court appearance on 29 August.